      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"6. SKETCHY DEMOS scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 6 lengths at this track in a handy 22.52 beating Silent Whisper. Awkwardly drawn but goes well at this distance. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. The one to beat again. 1. BUB WHO produced a modest effort most recently when fifth at Sandown over 515m behind Dash Intention (30.26) in a Grade 5. Was a winner the start prior. Has the ability to give this a shake. 4. SOUTH OF HEAVEN held his own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 2 lengths (22.65) behind Rabada at Ballarat. Expected to be in this for a long way. 2. SQUEEGEE'S RIDE is a surprise last-start placegetter who should be thereabouts.\",\"runners\":[6,1,4,2],\"exclusive\":false}",
